1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
And I want you to know that being here is a blessing to me.

2
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:10,279
As an older pastor, I, young ladies,

3
00:00:10,279 --> 00:00:12,859
that blesses my heart so much.

4
00:00:12,859 --> 00:00:14,520
That not only did you sing,

5
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:16,360
that is one of my favorite songs,

6
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:17,559
that is a beautiful song,

7
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:21,540
but then to be diligent in playing the instruments as well,

8
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:24,000
that is a wonderful, wonderful thing.

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,920
That encouraged this old preacher, okay?

10
00:00:26,920 --> 00:00:28,079
Thank you for that.

11
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,040
And then to see the sweetness

12
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:34,159
of the fellowship of this group.

13
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:37,360
I do not say this every church I go to,

14
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:40,439
and I don't say it to flatter you,

15
00:00:40,439 --> 00:00:43,599
but what you have here is special.

16
00:00:43,599 --> 00:00:45,880
And this is a wonderful church home.

17
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:49,000
You say, well, preacher, you don't know.

18
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,880
And I don't wanna know, okay?

19
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:54,240
I'm sure it's not perfect, you go here.

20
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:57,439
But I wanna tell you to have a church home

21
00:00:57,439 --> 00:01:01,479
where you're loved, where you learn the word of God,

22
00:01:01,479 --> 00:01:05,559
where young people serve.

23
00:01:05,559 --> 00:01:06,800
It is a special thing.

24
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,760
And I don't say that again to flatter.

25
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:11,040
I say that to encourage you

26
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:13,360
to protect what God has given you.

27
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:16,160
Participate in what God has given you.

28
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:18,199
Because these are not everywhere.

29
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:22,260
Man, I preach in a lot of places,

30
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:24,620
and these kinds of church homes,

31
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:26,160
these kinds of church families,

32
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:28,239
I'm gonna step out of my way here.

33
00:01:28,239 --> 00:01:32,199
This kind of preacher and his family are not everywhere.

34
00:01:32,199 --> 00:01:34,680
And so just appreciate what God has allowed you

35
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:39,400
to be a part of, and really give your all

36
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:41,519
to sharing it with other people.

37
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:42,900
There are a lot of people in this community

38
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:46,000
that need a family like this is a family.

39
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,919
So thank you, it's encouraged me, and I mean that.

40
00:01:48,919 --> 00:01:51,239
It's been an encouragement for me to be here.

41
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:54,680
Well, I met those 72-year-old newlyweds tonight,

42
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:58,639
and I told them my story about the 82-year-olds,

43
00:01:58,639 --> 00:02:00,720
and they said they're gonna pass that up, no problem.

44
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,839
So, amen.

45
00:02:02,839 --> 00:02:04,040
Take your Bible, if you would.

46
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,120
We're gonna go back to the Psalms one more time.

47
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,119
I promise, well, I'm not gonna promise,

48
00:02:08,119 --> 00:02:10,119
because the Lord may change my mind,

49
00:02:10,119 --> 00:02:12,720
but I will preach out of the New Testament

50
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:16,160
sometime this week, other than just Sunday school.

51
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:21,160
But the Psalms, I think, are very in tune for our times.

52
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:25,080
And I want you to know that we're going to Psalm 37 tonight.

53
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:28,080
I know that it is a well-known passage

54
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,720
that we're gonna study.

55
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:33,360
And to be quite frank with you, it's a very simple message,

56
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:37,940
but I think it has a very profound meaning and implication

57
00:02:37,940 --> 00:02:42,720
for where we find ourselves in our generation today.

58
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:46,820
And I simply want to preach for a few minutes tonight

59
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:50,320
on this thought, why fret?

60
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,839
Why fret?

61
00:02:51,839 --> 00:02:54,440
Boy, are we in a fretful generation.

62
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:57,600
Notice it with me in verse one, Psalm 37.

63
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,539
Again, a Psalm of David.

64
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:04,580
Fret not thyself because of evildoers,

65
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:09,759
neither be thou envious against the workers of iniquity,

66
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:14,080
for they shall soon be cut down like the grass

67
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:17,479
and wither as the green herb.

68
00:03:18,399 --> 00:03:22,479
Trust in the Lord and do good.

69
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:24,759
So shalt thou dwell in the land

70
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:27,020
and verily thou shalt be fed.

71
00:03:28,279 --> 00:03:31,600
Delight thyself also in the Lord

72
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:35,119
and he shall give thee the desires of thine heart.

73
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:38,839
Commit thy way unto the Lord.

74
00:03:38,839 --> 00:03:42,619
Trust also in him and he shall bring it to pass.

75
00:03:43,460 --> 00:03:48,059
And he shall bring forth thy righteousness as the light

76
00:03:48,059 --> 00:03:50,580
and thy judgment as the noonday.

77
00:03:51,619 --> 00:03:56,619
Rest in the Lord and wait patiently for him.

78
00:03:57,899 --> 00:04:02,899
Fret not thyself because of him who prospereth in his way,

79
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:08,240
because of the man who bringeth wicked devices to pass.

80
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:13,240
Cease from anger and forsake wrath.

81
00:04:13,399 --> 00:04:18,399
Fret not thyself in any wise to do evil.

82
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:23,640
I think God is saying something to us about fretting.

83
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,959
Don't you?

84
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:27,000
Let's pray and ask his help.

85
00:04:28,119 --> 00:04:29,959
Lord, I'm grateful for the time you've given us

86
00:04:29,959 --> 00:04:31,079
to be together tonight.

87
00:04:31,079 --> 00:04:34,119
And I'm very grateful for the privilege

88
00:04:34,119 --> 00:04:37,239
of being in this place, being with these people.

89
00:04:37,239 --> 00:04:39,239
Thank you for that, for myself.

90
00:04:40,239 --> 00:04:42,640
Lord, I pray now that you would use this time

91
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:45,339
and speak to our hearts from your word.

92
00:04:45,339 --> 00:04:46,920
Teach us truth tonight.

93
00:04:48,119 --> 00:04:50,399
And Lord, give us something that will help us

94
00:04:50,399 --> 00:04:55,399
navigate this bizarre generation we find ourselves in.

95
00:04:58,019 --> 00:05:01,160
Lord, above all, we want to be used of you

96
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:07,079
to try to be a help to those that are around us.

97
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,160
To try to point them to Christ.

98
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:16,040
And it is essential that we guard our testimonies,

99
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:21,040
our attitudes, so that they can see not the world in us

100
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,559
or a worldly reaction in us,

101
00:05:24,399 --> 00:05:26,839
but so that they can see Jesus Christ in us.

102
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:32,519
Help us tonight, I pray, in Jesus' name, amen.

103
00:05:34,119 --> 00:05:35,720
Why does the Bible address,

104
00:05:36,079 --> 00:05:38,600
my title is Why Fret?

105
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,640
And it doesn't mean why do we fret,

106
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:44,839
it means why does God address fretting?

107
00:05:44,839 --> 00:05:46,640
And I would suggest to you the reason

108
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:51,239
that God addresses fretting, names it by name three times

109
00:05:51,239 --> 00:05:55,480
in that passage I read, is because we're guilty of it.

110
00:05:56,600 --> 00:06:01,160
I think David was guilty of it at points of time in his life

111
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:04,519
and I think he realized as he was fretting

112
00:06:04,519 --> 00:06:06,720
that it was not pleasing to the Lord,

113
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:10,359
nor was it helpful to those that he was trying to lead

114
00:06:10,359 --> 00:06:14,279
or trying to minister to, for lack of a better term.

115
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:16,959
Sometimes I think we need to be very careful

116
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:21,959
to study specific words in our Bible reading

117
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:25,200
because there are shades of meaning

118
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:28,019
that maybe as we understand a word,

119
00:06:28,019 --> 00:06:30,140
we don't get the full implication

120
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,519
of what God is saying to us.

121
00:06:32,519 --> 00:06:34,040
And I want you to understand tonight

122
00:06:34,559 --> 00:06:37,000
that fret is such a word.

123
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:41,399
When God tells us to fret not,

124
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:44,959
somehow in my mind I have the picture of fretting

125
00:06:44,959 --> 00:06:49,720
as not real big worry, just little worry.

126
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:52,040
Just kind of bothered by it and you know,

127
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,040
you know I'm twiddling my fingers

128
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,880
and I'm a little bothered by that.

129
00:06:56,739 --> 00:06:59,559
But I want you to understand that's not the full meaning

130
00:06:59,559 --> 00:07:01,720
that God is saying.

131
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:05,720
What God is saying when he uses the word korah,

132
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:08,000
which is translated fret not,

133
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:13,839
it has the meaning of to be so consumed by something

134
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,760
that it makes us very angry.

135
00:07:17,899 --> 00:07:20,380
To be so consumed by something

136
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:23,440
that it changes our countenance.

137
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:26,200
To be so consumed by something

138
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:31,079
that it changes our perspective and our attitude.

139
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:35,679
It guides our response instead of the spirit

140
00:07:35,679 --> 00:07:38,320
guiding our reaction or response.

141
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:42,920
And it can be such a something that we're so angry about

142
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:46,359
that it also instills and we live in fear

143
00:07:46,359 --> 00:07:48,440
of that thing in our life.

144
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:52,880
And so God is saying, listen, I want you to be careful

145
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:56,959
that you don't allow seeing something in life

146
00:07:56,959 --> 00:08:00,880
that makes you so fearful or so angry

147
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,200
that it changes your countenance

148
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:08,200
and changes your response, your reaction to that thing.

149
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,899
First question I ask tonight is this.

150
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:17,040
What is it that we fret about?

151
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:22,079
What makes us so angry as we live in this generation?

152
00:08:22,079 --> 00:08:24,399
What is it that we're so fearful about

153
00:08:24,399 --> 00:08:27,440
that we get angry and we get upset about it?

154
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,519
Let me mention a few things.

155
00:08:29,519 --> 00:08:32,000
And I think this is first, maybe for my life,

156
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,460
and I hope you can identify in it too.

157
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:40,520
I fret over, I get upset with unfair things in life.

158
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,520
Unfairness.

159
00:08:45,039 --> 00:08:49,320
Verse one tells us not to be envious

160
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:52,219
against the workers of iniquity.

161
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:56,200
I don't know about you, but it's easy to get upset

162
00:08:56,239 --> 00:09:00,880
when people who seem to totally disregard God

163
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:04,840
seem to live prosperous, ideal lives.

164
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:07,640
Now maybe you have achieved perfection.

165
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,739
I'm not there yet.

166
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:14,239
And it still bothers me when I see people

167
00:09:14,239 --> 00:09:18,119
who completely disregard the Lord,

168
00:09:18,119 --> 00:09:20,859
have no space for the Lord in their life,

169
00:09:20,859 --> 00:09:24,359
no fear of the Lord, no respect for his word,

170
00:09:24,359 --> 00:09:28,840
and yet it seems like in life they seem to prosper.

171
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,559
I don't think I'm alone in that.

172
00:09:30,559 --> 00:09:33,440
As a matter of fact, I can give you a number of examples

173
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,679
in the Old Testament.

174
00:09:34,679 --> 00:09:38,619
I can find Habakkuk, that great prophet.

175
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:39,960
Preacher, you know one of the things

176
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:42,320
I always wished for as a pastor?

177
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:47,320
People would name their sons Levi and Elijah and Joseph.

178
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:50,520
I could never get a Habakkuk out of our congregation.

179
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:51,419
I don't know why.

180
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:56,140
Habakkuk cried out to the Lord and was upset with the Lord

181
00:09:56,140 --> 00:10:00,059
because God seemed to be prospering the Chaldeans.

182
00:10:00,059 --> 00:10:09,459
Babylon was prospering against Jerusalem and God was allowing Babylon to persecute the

183
00:10:09,459 --> 00:10:16,219
Jew in Jerusalem and the Hebrew and Habakkuk got very upset with the Lord about that.

184
00:10:16,219 --> 00:10:18,259
How can you allow that, Lord?

185
00:10:18,259 --> 00:10:26,179
How, God, can you allow pagans to prosper when your own people are suffering?

186
00:10:26,179 --> 00:10:30,379
I'll tell you how mad Jonah got about it.

187
00:10:30,379 --> 00:10:37,619
Jonah got so angry with the Lord wanting to offer repentance and salvation or reformation

188
00:10:37,619 --> 00:10:45,899
to the Ninevites that Jonah ran away from the Lord even after he obeyed the Lord and

189
00:10:45,899 --> 00:10:51,859
went to Nineveh and he saw the Ninevites repent and he saw God bless their land.

190
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:53,579
You remember what he did, don't you?

191
00:10:53,579 --> 00:10:58,979
He went up on the hill outside the city and pouted and was mad with God because God did

192
00:10:58,979 --> 00:11:01,219
something he didn't want him to do.

193
00:11:01,219 --> 00:11:04,860
He did something that he thought was unfair.

194
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:12,139
How can these violent people who oppose everything you are, God, and everything you tell me to

195
00:11:12,139 --> 00:11:19,979
be in your word, how can these violent people be allowed to exist, be allowed to prosper

196
00:11:20,259 --> 00:11:26,459
while so many of ours seem to suffer?

197
00:11:26,459 --> 00:11:27,459
How about this?

198
00:11:27,459 --> 00:11:31,779
Let's flip it around and let's examine a life like Job.

199
00:11:31,779 --> 00:11:36,419
Job, a man who truly feared the Lord.

200
00:11:36,419 --> 00:11:43,059
Job, a man who tried to be very careful to conduct his life in such a way as to honor

201
00:11:43,059 --> 00:11:50,819
the Lord and then we watch that man decimated in his possessions, decimated in his family,

202
00:11:50,819 --> 00:11:57,059
decimated in his own health and I'm just going to confess to you that sometimes even as much

203
00:11:57,059 --> 00:12:04,220
as I have studied the Word, sometimes I'm just, I wonder God, why?

204
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:08,539
Why is that allowed to happen?

205
00:12:08,539 --> 00:12:16,380
I think one of the things we have to do is remember the perspective of verse 2.

206
00:12:16,380 --> 00:12:24,419
For they shall soon be cut down like the grass and wither as the green herb.

207
00:12:24,419 --> 00:12:30,099
Get this statement, it's not deep but I think it will help.

208
00:12:30,099 --> 00:12:37,459
Life always works out like God says it will.

209
00:12:37,459 --> 00:12:44,459
Life always works out like God says it will.

210
00:12:44,459 --> 00:12:52,699
I learned years ago that you had to be very careful about how you viewed our world and

211
00:12:52,699 --> 00:12:55,699
your life and what perspective you took.

212
00:12:55,699 --> 00:13:02,580
If we're not careful, we take a snapshot view of life.

213
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:10,479
We look at the moment that has got our attention and we make judgments about those lives based

214
00:13:10,479 --> 00:13:13,020
on that snapshot.

215
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:19,380
It's like we walk around with a mind that is a Polaroid and we take the shot and we

216
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:25,419
make the judgment about that thing at that moment on that and I don't know if this is

217
00:13:25,419 --> 00:13:32,139
a good analogy for a Fundamental Baptist pulpit but life is a full run movie.

218
00:13:32,139 --> 00:13:38,819
And I have finally learned that the snapshot doesn't often tell the story, that you've

219
00:13:38,819 --> 00:13:45,500
got to watch the full run of that life and the full run that proceeds from that event

220
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:54,619
and what you will learn at the end of that movie is that God is always right and what

221
00:13:54,619 --> 00:14:02,899
God says will be will always be and the wicked never, ever, ever prosper.

222
00:14:02,899 --> 00:14:06,220
They never do.

223
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:15,059
And you and I, when we allow ourselves to have hearts that get angry or get fearful

224
00:14:15,059 --> 00:14:21,980
because of that moment in time, we end up interfering our entire relationship with the

225
00:14:21,980 --> 00:14:27,459
Lord, our entire relationship perhaps with our family, our relationship with our church

226
00:14:27,459 --> 00:14:31,220
because we have looked at a moment in the wrong perspective.

227
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:32,220
Let me give you this example.

228
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:39,820
For the sake of time I won't take you to Luke chapter 16 but in Luke chapter 16 a wonderful

229
00:14:39,820 --> 00:14:46,899
story is given to us and it's the story of Lazarus and the rich man.

230
00:14:46,899 --> 00:14:52,820
And Lazarus, that man was in such miserable shape in his life.

231
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:59,980
He was lame, he was covered with sores, he had no source evidently of a family that could

232
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:06,779
feed him or care for him and he sat daily at the door of that rich man and it says that

233
00:15:06,779 --> 00:15:13,899
his highest aspiration was that he could eat of the crumbs of that rich man's table.

234
00:15:13,899 --> 00:15:20,579
That rich man is described to us as one who fared sumptually, who dressed in a regal way

235
00:15:20,579 --> 00:15:27,179
and my interpretation of that is, as I see him, is that he cared little for Lazarus being

236
00:15:27,179 --> 00:15:35,700
there and if ever, not often, gave to his needs and just walked past him uncaring.

237
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:38,000
And we might sit there and say why?

238
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:43,779
How does God allow that until we get the end of the story?

239
00:15:43,779 --> 00:15:46,820
And what do we find at the end of the story?

240
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:52,940
We find that Lazarus, that poor man who has suffered for those years of life is now in

241
00:15:52,940 --> 00:15:59,540
the bosom of Abraham and now enjoys the blessing of being in the presence of the Lord and the

242
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:05,739
blessings of the eternal state and we find that rich man not wearing his regal robes

243
00:16:05,739 --> 00:16:12,619
and not faring sumptuously in hell and we find him pleading, please can Lazarus just

244
00:16:12,619 --> 00:16:17,700
dip his finger in water and just touch my tongue with that drop?

245
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:21,459
