721
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:19,800
God knows where we are and I want you to know that God wants to be a help to us.

722
00:48:19,800 --> 00:48:22,800
So do what God tells you to do.

723
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:28,440
As we conclude our prayer and as we offer an invitation, let God help you.

724
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:30,440
Seek His help tonight.

725
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:33,000
Father, we are just people.

726
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:34,440
We're dust.

727
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:36,679
You know we are.

728
00:48:36,679 --> 00:48:42,960
And yet you are so patient and long-suffering and merciful towards us that you'll meet us

729
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:45,799
in these moments.

730
00:48:45,799 --> 00:48:52,160
And Lord, we don't want to be that critic, that complainer, that angry person.

731
00:48:52,160 --> 00:48:57,400
We want to be that person that just has the testimony of trusting the Lord no matter how

732
00:48:57,400 --> 00:49:01,160
difficult the circumstances seem.

733
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:08,840
So Lord, we want that not only for our own contentment, but because this is a hurting,

734
00:49:08,840 --> 00:49:13,520
hurting, fearful, angry world.

735
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:20,160
They need to see somebody who can point them to the Lord where they can have peace in their

736
00:49:20,160 --> 00:49:21,559
hearts.

737
00:49:21,559 --> 00:49:24,760
Help us to be the picture of that peace, I pray.

738
00:49:24,760 --> 00:49:27,320
In Jesus' name, amen.

739
00:49:27,320 --> 00:49:28,720
Would you quietly stand to your feet?

